com.scalien.scaliendb
Class StringRangeParams

java.lang.Object
  com.scalien.scaliendb.StringRangeParams

public class StringRangeParams
extends java.lang.Object

StringRangeParams is a convenient way to specify the string parameters for iteration when using Table.getKeyIterator(StringRangeParams), Table.getKeyValueIterator(StringRangeParams) and Table.count(StringRangeParams).

The supported parameters are:

  • prefix
  • start key
  • end key
  • count

StringRangeParams is convenient because is uses chaining, so you can write expressions like new StringRangeParams().prefix(prefix).startKey(startKey).endKey(endKey).count(count) and it returns the StringRangeParams instance.

The default values are empty strings.

Example: 

 // print keys that start with "foo", starting at "foobar"
 for (String key : client.getKeyIterator(new StringRangeParams().prefix("foo").startKey("foobar")))
     System.out.println(key);

See Also:
Table.getKeyIterator(StringRangeParams), Table.getKeyValueIterator(StringRangeParams), Table.count(StringRangeParams)
